        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rate Limiting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tool rate limiting prevents an agent from overwhelming external services, exhausting API quotas, sending excessive emails, or issuing too many write operations in a short window. Without it, a reasoning loop that gets stuck can call "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "search_web"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " hundreds of times in a single conversation, or a billing tool can be called repeatedly until a quota or cost ceiling is hit. Rate limiting is a safety control, not a performance optimisation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Token bucket rate limiting model with per-tool limits and session budget",
          "title": "Tool Rate Limiting Token Bucket"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Return RATE_LIMITED immediately when a limit is exceeded — do not sleep inside the handler. The model reads the result and decides whether to wait, tell the user, or try a different approach."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Token Bucket Implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A token bucket allows bursts up to the bucket capacity while enforcing an average rate. Each tool call consumes one token; tokens refill at a fixed rate. When the bucket is empty, the call is rejected."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import time\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom threading import Lock\nfrom typing import Any\n\n@dataclass\nclass TokenBucket:\n    capacity: int          # maximum tokens (burst size)\n    refill_rate: float     # tokens per second\n    _tokens: float = field(init=False)\n    _last_refill: float = field(init=False)\n    _lock: Lock = field(default_factory=Lock, repr=False)\n\n    def __post_init__(self) -> None:\n        self._tokens = float(self.capacity)\n        self._last_refill = time.monotonic()\n\n    def consume(self, n: float = 1.0) -> tuple[bool, float]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Try to consume n tokens.\n        Returns (allowed, retry_after_seconds).\n        retry_after_seconds is 0.0 if allowed.\n        \"\"\"\n        with self._lock:\n            now = time.monotonic()\n            elapsed = now - self._last_refill\n            self._tokens = min(\n                self.capacity,\n                self._tokens + elapsed * self.refill_rate,\n            )\n            self._last_refill = now\n\n            if self._tokens >= n:\n                self._tokens -= n\n                return True, 0.0\n\n            # Time until n tokens are available\n            wait = (n - self._tokens) / self.refill_rate\n            return False, round(wait, 1)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "_lock"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " makes the bucket thread-safe for multi-threaded agents. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "retry_after_seconds"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is returned to the caller rather than sleeping inside the method — the caller decides whether to wait or surface the limit to the model."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Per-Tool Rate Limit Registry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Define limits per tool and scope buckets per session so different conversations do not share quota."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from collections import defaultdict\n\n# Tool-level rate limits: (capacity, refill_rate_per_second)\nTOOL_RATE_LIMITS: dict[str, tuple[int, float]] = {\n    \"search_web\":       (10, 10/60),   # 10 burst, 10 per minute\n    \"fetch_page\":       (10, 10/60),\n    \"create_refund\":    (5,  5/60),    # 5 burst, 5 per minute\n    \"send_email\":       (3,  3/60),    # 3 burst, 3 per minute\n    \"export_data\":      (2,  2/60),    # 2 burst, 2 per minute\n    \"update_status\":    (20, 20/60),\n}\n_DEFAULT_LIMIT = (30, 30/60)   # fallback for unlisted tools\n\nclass RateLimitRegistry:\n    \"\"\"Holds per-(session, tool) token buckets.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self) -> None:\n        # { session_id -> { tool_name -> TokenBucket } }\n        self._buckets: dict[str, dict[str, TokenBucket]] = defaultdict(dict)\n\n    def check(\n        self, session_id: str, tool_name: str\n    ) -> tuple[bool, float]:\n        buckets = self._buckets[session_id]\n        if tool_name not in buckets:\n            cap, rate = TOOL_RATE_LIMITS.get(tool_name, _DEFAULT_LIMIT)\n            buckets[tool_name] = TokenBucket(capacity=cap, refill_rate=rate)\n        return buckets[tool_name].consume()\n\n_RATE_REGISTRY = RateLimitRegistry()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Session Budget — Hard Ceilings"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A per-session budget caps the total number of tool calls, write operations, and cost within a single conversation. Unlike token buckets (which recover over time), budgets are absolute: once exhausted, the agent stops calling tools entirely for that session."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass SessionBudget:\n    max_total_calls: int   = 200\n    max_write_calls: int   = 20\n    max_cost_usd: float    = 2.00\n    total_calls: int       = 0\n    write_calls: int       = 0\n    cost_usd: float        = 0.0\n\n    # Tools classified as writes (cost more budget)\n    WRITE_TOOLS: frozenset[str] = frozenset({\n        \"create_refund\", \"void_invoice\", \"send_email\",\n        \"update_status\", \"export_data\", \"enqueue_review\",\n    })\n\n    def check_and_record(\n        self,\n        tool_name: str,\n        estimated_cost_usd: float = 0.0,\n    ) -> dict[str, Any] | None:\n        \"\"\"\n        Returns an error dict if budget is exceeded, else None.\n        Records the call if allowed.\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.total_calls >= self.max_total_calls:\n            return {\"error\": \"RATE_LIMITED\",\n                    \"message\": \"Session tool-call budget exhausted (200 calls).\",\n                    \"retry_after_seconds\": None}   # None = no retry; start new session\n        if tool_name in self.WRITE_TOOLS and self.write_calls >= self.max_write_calls:\n            return {\"error\": \"RATE_LIMITED\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Session write budget exhausted ({self.max_write_calls} writes).\",\n                    \"retry_after_seconds\": None}\n        if self.cost_usd + estimated_cost_usd > self.max_cost_usd:\n            return {\"error\": \"RATE_LIMITED\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Session cost budget (${self.max_cost_usd:.2f}) would be exceeded.\",\n                    \"retry_after_seconds\": None}\n        # Record\n        self.total_calls += 1\n        if tool_name in self.WRITE_TOOLS:\n            self.write_calls += 1\n        self.cost_usd += estimated_cost_usd\n        return None"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating Rate Limiting into Dispatch"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rate checks run before the handler executes. Both the per-tool bucket and the session budget are checked; either can reject the call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import logging\n\n_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ndef dispatch_with_rate_limit(\n    tool_name: str,\n    inputs: dict[str, Any],\n    session_id: str,\n    budget: SessionBudget,\n    registry,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    # 1. Session budget check\n    budget_err = budget.check_and_record(tool_name)\n    if budget_err:\n        _LOG.warning(\"budget_exceeded session=%s tool=%s\", session_id, tool_name)\n        return budget_err\n\n    # 2. Per-tool rate limit check\n    allowed, retry_after = _RATE_REGISTRY.check(session_id, tool_name)\n    if not allowed:\n        _LOG.warning(\n            \"rate_limited session=%s tool=%s retry_after=%.1fs\",\n            session_id, tool_name, retry_after,\n        )\n        return {\n            \"error\": \"RATE_LIMITED\",\n            \"message\": f\"Tool '{tool_name}' rate limit exceeded. Try again in {retry_after}s.\",\n            \"retry_after_seconds\": retry_after,\n        }\n\n    # 3. Execute\n    tool_def = registry.get(tool_name)\n    if tool_def is None:\n        return {\"error\": \"NOT_FOUND\", \"message\": f\"Tool '{tool_name}' not found\"}\n    return tool_def.handler(**inputs)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "retry_after_seconds"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a non-None number, the model can mention to the user that the tool will be available again shortly. When it is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "None"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (budget exhausted), the model should end the conversation or ask the user to start a new one."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Exponential Backoff for External Limits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When your tool calls an external API that returns a 429, handle it in the tool handler rather than surfacing it immediately. Retry once with the provider's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Retry-After"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " delay (if ≤ 30s), then return "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "RATE_LIMITED"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " if still failing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import time\nimport requests\n\ndef _call_with_backoff(\n    session: requests.Session,\n    method: str,\n    url: str,\n    max_retries: int = 2,\n    **kwargs,\n) -> requests.Response:\n    \"\"\"\n    Retry on 429 / 503 up to max_retries times, respecting Retry-After.\n    Does NOT sleep longer than 30 seconds per retry.\n    \"\"\"\n    for attempt in range(max_retries + 1):\n        resp = session.request(method, url, **kwargs)\n        if resp.status_code not in (429, 503) or attempt == max_retries:\n            return resp\n        retry_after = float(resp.headers.get(\"Retry-After\", 2 ** attempt))\n        if retry_after > 30:\n            return resp   # too long to wait; caller will surface RATE_LIMITED\n        time.sleep(retry_after)\n    return resp   # unreachable but satisfies type checker"
          }
        ]
      },
